---
import SAGPLayout from "../../layouts/SAGPLayout.astro";
import PageHero from "../../components/PageHero.astro";
---

<SAGPLayout title="Who We Are | Society for Ancient Greek Philosophy">

<PageHero
  kicker="Who We Are"
  title="A conversation about Ancient Greek philosophy since 1953."
  subtitle="The Society for Ancient Greek Philosophy is an international community of scholars and students devoted to rigorous inquiry, scholarly exchange, and the continuing life of Ancient Greek philosophy."
  image="/assets/images/delphi_treasury.jpg"
/>

<section class="section two-col">
  <div>
    <h2>Our beginning</h2>
  </div>
  <div>
    <p>
      The Society for Ancient Greek Philosophy was established on December 28,
      1953, in Rochester, New York, and was initially known as the Presocratic
      Society.
    </p>
    <p>
      The idea for the Society began with a conversation between George Burch,
      Constantine Cavernos, and R. K. Sprague at a meeting of the Eastern
      Division of the American Philosophical Association in 1952.
    </p>
    <div class="callout">
      The Society began, fittingly, with a conversation — and conversation
      remains at the heart of its scholarly life.
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section">
  <h2>What the Society does</h2>

  <div class="card-grid">
    <article class="card">
      <h3>Scholarly conferences</h3>
      <p>
        SAGP organizes annual conferences and sponsors panels with major
        philosophical and classical associations.
      </p>
    </article>

    <article class="card">
      <h3>Works in progress</h3>
      <p>
        The Society encourages scholars, especially early-career and mid-career
        scholars, to present developing work and receive thoughtful feedback.
      </p>
    </article>

    <article class="card">
      <h3>Distinguished scholarship</h3>
      <p>
        The Distinguished Lectureship recognizes scholars whose work has made
        substantial contributions to the field.
      </p>
    </article>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section two-col">
  <div>
    <h2>Our aim</h2>
  </div>
  <div>
    <p>
      SAGP encourages and contributes to the scholarly study of Ancient Greek
      Philosophy, primarily in the analytic tradition, but also in other
      traditions developed in Europe and other parts of the world.
    </p>
    <p>
      By collaborating with other associations, SAGP furthers research,
      facilitates interactions among international scholars, and highlights the
      interdisciplinary and intercultural dimensions of the field.
    </p>
    <p>
      SAGP is especially proactive in encouraging junior and mid-career scholars
      to present their work and is strongly committed to promoting equality and
      diversity in the field of Ancient Greek Philosophy.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section">
  <h2>Institutional virtues</h2>

  <div class="card-grid">
    <article class="card">
      <h3>Scholarly excellence</h3>
      <p>Rigorous research, careful argument, and serious engagement with ancient texts.</p>
    </article>

    <article class="card">
      <h3>Intellectual generosity</h3>
      <p>Constructive feedback, mentorship, and conversation across career stages.</p>
    </article>

    <article class="card">
      <h3>International openness</h3>
      <p>A growing community of scholars across countries, disciplines, and traditions.</p>
    </article>
  </div>
</section>


</SAGPLayout>
